// Named splice anchor §4 (M43), the rule-free case: a malformed `@Undeclared();`
// site must be rejected even when the program contains NO rules at all — M43 is a
// property of the site (a name that is not a declared attribute), not of any
// targeting rule. Regression guard for the splice-index validation running
// unconditionally, not only inside the rules path.
string addRoutes() {
    string sink = "x";
    @Undeclared();
    return sink;
}

console.writeln(addRoutes());
